“computer  network”  means  the  interconnection  of  communication 
lines and circuits with a computer or a complex consisting of two or 
more interconnected computers;

“data” means representations of information or of concepts that are 
being prepared or have been prepared in a form suitable for use in a 
computer;

“function” includes logic, control, arithmetic, deletion, storage and 
retrieval and communication or telecommunication to, from or within 
a computer;

(b) copies or moves it to any storage medium other than that in 
which  it  is  held  or  to  a  different  location  in  the  storage 
medium in which it is  held;

(a) he causes a computer to perform any function with intent to  
secure    access    to    any    program    or    data    held    in    any 
computer;
